children.subject: As someone who was sadly dropped from the course, I can confirm that EE16A has indeed been cancelled for this summer. As for course alternatives, I'll leave the student response open for anyone else to respond.
I was in EE16A and got dropped. I put myself on the waitlist for CS188, CS160, and CS61C because I still wanted to fulfill one of my CS reqs over the summer. I got into CS188 this morning.

history.content:
EE16A and EE16B were canceled for this summer as there are no instructors available to teach the course.

If you're declared in another COE major, I recommend checking in with your ESS advisor. You can find the degree requirements here: https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/eecs/degree-reqs. You'll need to make progress in the lower-division classes, if you plan to switch into EECS from another COE major or double major.

Was the summer 16A class dropped? It looks like no one is enrolled or on the waitlist anymore on http://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2018-summer-eleng-16a-001-lec-001

If this class is not available for the summer, what class should I take instead if I want to pursue changing my major to or double majoring in EECS?
history.subject: Summer EE16A
